Inference for linear functional in the high dimensional logistic regression model

LF_logistic.Rd

Computes the bias corrected estimator of the linear functional loading\(^{\top}\beta\) for the high dimensional logistic regression model \(Y_i|X_i \sim \) Bernoulli\((\frac{e^{X_i^{\top}\beta}}{1+e^{X_i^{\top}\beta}})\) and the corresponding standard error.

LF_logistic(
  X,
  y,
  loading,
  weight,
  intercept = TRUE,
  init.Lasso = NULL,
  mu = NULL,
  step = NULL,
  resol = 1.5,
  maxiter = 10
)

Arguments

X

Design matrix, of dimension \(n\) x \(p\)
y

Outcome vector, of length \(n\)
loading

Loading, of length \(p\)
weight

The weight vector, of length \(n\), used in correcting the plug-in estimator
intercept

Should intercept(s) be fitted (default = TRUE)
init.Lasso

Initial LASSO estimator of the regression vector (default = NULL)
mu

The tuning parameter in construction of the projection direction (default = NULL)
step

Number of steps (< maxiter) to obtain the smallest mu that gives convergence of the optimization problem for constructing the projection direction (default = NULL)
resol

Resolution or the factor by which mu is increased/decreased to obtain the smallest mu that gives convergence of the optimization problem of constructing the projection direction (default = 1.5)
maxiter

Maximum number of steps along which mu is increased/decreased to obtain the smallest mu that gives convergence of the optimization problem for constructing the projection direction (default = 10)

Value

prop.est

The bias corrected estimator of the linear functional

se

Standard error of the bias-corrected estimator

proj

The projection direction, of length \(p\)

plug.in

Plug-in LASSO estimator of the linear functional

References

Guo Z, Rakshit P, Herman DS, Chen J (2019). “Inference for Case Probability in High-dimensional Logistic Regression.” Unknown.

Examples

A1gen <- function(rho,p){
A1=matrix(0,p,p)
for(i in 1:p){
  for(j in 1:p){
    A1[i,j]<-rho^(abs(i-j))
  }
}
A1
}
n = 100
p = 400
mu <- rep(0,p)
rho = 0.5
Cov <- (A1gen(rho,p))/2
Cov2<-matrix(NA,nrow=p,ncol=p)
for(i in 1:p){
  for(j in 1:p){
    Cov2[i,j]<-0.5^(1+abs(i-j))
  }
}
beta <- rep(0,p)
beta[1:10] <- c(1:10)/5
X <- MASS::mvrnorm(n,mu,Cov)
exp_val <- X%*%beta
prob <- exp(exp_val)/(1+exp(exp_val))
y <- rbinom(n,1,prob)
loading <- MASS::mvrnorm(1,mu,Cov2)
LF_logistic(X = X, y = y, loading = loading, intercept = TRUE, weight = rep(1,n))
